Package runnables

Class SampleAnalyserRunnable

java.lang.Object
runnables.SampleAnalyserRunnable
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public final class SampleAnalyserRunnable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
Implementation of the Runnable interface to analyze a sample.

Runs a sample analysis in a single thread.

Since:
2.0
Version:
2.0
Author:
Simon Hackl

  • Constructor Details

    • SampleAnalyserRunnable

      public SampleAnalyserRunnable​(java.lang.String sampleName, ReferenceAnalysisEntry referenceAnalysisEntry, htsjdk.samtools.util.CloseableIterator<htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.VariantContext> variantInformation, VariablePositionsTable variablePositionsTable, double minCoverage, double minFrequency, double minQuality, me.tongfei.progressbar.ProgressBar progress)
      Constructor of SampleAnalyserRunnable.
      Parameters:
      sampleName - String the samples name.
      referenceAnalysisEntry - ReferenceAnalysisEntry information about the reference to which respect the sample is analyzed.
      variantInformation - htsjdk.samtools.util.CloseableIterator<htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.VariantContext> returned by a VCFFileReader giving access to the single input `.vcf` files entries.
      variablePositionsTable - VariablePositionsTable to store the processed information.
      minCoverage - Double minimum coverage specified by the user.
      minFrequency - Double minimum frequency specified by the user. This may only be relevant if multiple alleles are possible.
      minQuality - Double minimum quality specified by the user.
      progress - ProgressBar to indicate runtime information.

      referenceAllele - Allele the reference allele information.

    • assignBase

      private char assignBase​(char alternativeBase, double quality, double coverage, double frequency)
      Internal method to assign the correct content symbol based on the called base, quality, coverage and frequency.

      See the implementation of VariablePosition for all possible contents.

      Parameters:
      alternativeBase - Character the called alternative base.
      quality - Double the quality of the base call.
      coverage - Double the coverage of the base call.
      frequency - Double the frequency of the base call.
      Returns:
      A Character representing the variant content.
